description.narrative: Established in 2003 in Geneva Switzerland DNDi’s headquarters office is active in Research & Development activities as well as in administrative and support departments, including finance human resources, IT, policy advocacy, communications and external relations.

Teams manage projects and partnerships so that new and adapted treatments are developed for sleeping sickness, leishmaniasis, Chagas disease, paediatric HIV, filarial diseases, mycetoma and hepatitis C. From 2016 until 2018 DNDi Geneva incubated the WHO-DNDi joint initiative Global Antibiotic Research & Development Partnership (GARDP).
